On 12-30-2011 SAR personnel were called out for a missing Alzheimer's patient who walked away from his care home in Klamath Falls.  16 SAR members divided up into four trucks and four quadrants and began their road search.  At the same time a K9 air scent team was deployed at the IPP and followed the subjects trail in the urban neighborhood.  The K9 team member found a boot print and soon the subjects a coat entangled in a fence eventually tracking the subject to the field behind a school.  The subject was found in a ditch in a hypothermic state with skin lacerations due to falling as well bumps and bruises.  He was transported to Sky Lakes Medical Center.

83 yo male with early Alzheimer's, went for his daily walk in the neighborhood and told his wife that he may head up to the forest service road at the end of their street.  After 20 minutes went by, which is his usual time limit before his knees and feet get sore, and he did not return home, his wife and son went out looking for him and in the area and could not locate him.  911 was called and Newport Police arrived on scene and started driving the roads in the neighborhood and unable to locate subject.  SAR was called to assist and I arrived and interviewed family and determined that his likely location would be in the forested area since the homes and yards of the neighboring houses did not turn up any sign.  Subject was located about 1 mile from his home by SAR ground personnel doing sound sweeps.  Subject had slid from the roadway 110 ft down over an embankment into a heavy brush area and was calling for help.  Subject thought he was only a couple hundred feet from his home when he started sliding down the hill.

An 86 year old male with Alzheimer's snuck out of his residence.  He was last seen by his elderly wife at approximately 12:00 hrs.  He was noticed missing by his grand daughter, who looked for him.  He wasn't found and failed to return home, so 911 was called.  A search was initiated, and teams were deployed into the field to look.  A 4x4 unit on containment was approached by an unknown citizen, who had the missing subject with them.  The male was dropped off and the citizen departed before any information was obtained on where he was found.  The missing subject was unable to say where he had been as he had advanced Alzheimer's.

Subject walked away from his doctor's appointment traveling 4.5 miles to a location he used to reside.  Upon arrival subject knocked on the door asking for help.  Salem Police attempted for two hours to locate subject then requested the assistance of MCSO-SAR.

Portland Police requested assistance from a trailing canine to search for an elderly woman with dementia who had left her home.  There was about seven hours from reported time missing to start of canine track.  The canine tracked approximately 1.2 miles from the home to the MAX station at N Interstate and N Albina where the track went cold.  Later that afternoon, the subject wandered into a business in inner southeast Portland saying she was lost.  Police were not able to ascertain how she came to arrive at the business.

[Subject], 75 year-old female, with severe stage of Dementia wandered away from elderly care facility located in Tigard, OR.  She was physically fit and left wearing a short sleeve shirt, capri pants, and loafer shoes.  She had a purse with her but no phone or identification.  She had moved into the facility only a few days earlier and was not familiar with the area.  A citizen later called in and advised that there was a confused female in her yard in Tualatin, OR.  The female turned out to be [Subject] and she was returned to the family near the care facility.  [Subject] had walked about 4.7 miles.

Mutual aid to Linn County for a 62 yr old female who had a domestic with her husband and walked away from their home.  Hid in a nasty abandoned trailer that was covered 14ft in blackberry vines.  Woke up in the morning and walked back home to feed the dogs.

Subject was observed in his driveway removing trees from the heavy snow and rain fall.  The next day family came to take the subject to the doctors office and they found his residence with out power and ransacked with the back door open.  There were footprints that led to the back tree line and then they were lost in the brush.  Subject was located by searchers in critical condition with severe hypothermia.

At approximately 2115 hours April 13, 2012 [subject] was reported missing from his hotel room after he told his wife he was going to his car to get his prescriptions.  SAR was dispatched just after midnight and searched surrounding streets and around outside of buildings until approximately 0900 the next day.  SAR K9 alerted on the upstairs floor next door to the man's room, but was disregarded because the room was too close to his own room.  After talking with the hotel manager, the rooms were all checked and [subject] was found asleep in the nearby room that his room key had been able to open.

On May 7, 2012, [subject] who suffers from Alzheimer's Disease, left on foot from his residence.  His family followed but where unable to locate.  He has gone missing several times over the last two years and knows the area well.  Teams searched around the subject's home and outbuildings and vehicles.  They then were driven south where a K9 showed interest in a 5" circle near a tree.  Later the subjects comb and cup were found and he was located just before dark.

Project Lifesaver Client reported as missing.  Project Lifesaver "Client Handler" and a Deputy responded to assist Bend PD with the search for missing male.  PLS client was located by an area resident prior to SAR being deployed to the scene.  Client was in good condition and was returned home by DCSO patrol.

On 06/04/12 at 1638 hrs, I was contacted for a SAR assist in Tigard on a missing endangered dementia male name [subject].  He left his residence at approximately 1300 hrs.  I assisted with a missing person interview and outside resources to help locate [subject] who left on foot.  NORSAR assisted with a canine track that lead them to Pacific Highway when the track went cold.  [subject] was checked into a hotel by a good Samaritan who paid for the room.  [subject] stayed at the hotel for a while then traveled to Mazatlan restaurant where he hung out for a few hours.  [subject] then returned on his own to his residence at 2200 hrs.  The total distance traveled round trip was 2.37 miles.

On 05/30/2012 at about 2326 hours, CCSO was notified of a missing Dementia subject in Happy Valley, Oregon who walked away from her home and did not return.  A search of the immediate area was conducted by patrol vehicles but the subject was not located.  CCSO SAR was contacted on 05/31/2012 and contacted volunteer resources and responded to the scene to do a more thorough search.  Prior to resources arriving, the missing female was located at Portland Adventist Hospital where she had been dropped off.
Assisted City with search for missing Alzheimer's male subject.  OSP located subject walking on the freeway.

Locate a missing dementia patient from his case facility.  He was located next door in an auto wrecking yard sitting behind the steering wheel of a wrecked car trying to start it.  He was uninjured and returned to his care facility.

Subject walked away from his residence in Veneta. He had Stage four and five of dementia and Parkinson's disease. Family searched the area and was not able to find him. We arrived and searched the area with k-9 and was able to track to Highway 126. We were informed that the person travelled on the local bus service to Eugene then attempted to take the Grey hound bus to Salem but was turned away. The subject was located by local citizens near the LTD bus transfer station in Eugene and returned to his family in good health.

An 82 year old dementia patient was brought to Providence Medical Center located at NE 55th and NE Glisan St. for an appointment.  He was transported there by Metro West and was to be picked up at 1530.  When they got there the patient had wandered off.  The report came out approx 6 hours after this happened.  A canine team was requested and three NORSAR personnel responded.  They tracked from the hospital to the areas of NE 31st and Laurelhurst and to the bowling alley around 35th and Halsey St.  At that time, the dogs lost the track and PPB called off the search.

On 9/11/12 at about 1547 hours, I was called out from home on a report of a missing female hiker.  Information was Missing Person(MP) was hiking with her husband from the Whitewater trailhead.  Husband was at the trailhead waiting for us to respond.  He reported MP was following him back down the trail towards the parking lot when they were separated.  He said she was right behind him and when he looked back five minutes later, she was not behind him.  He went back up the trail calling for her but had negative results.  He finished out the trail, left in his vehicle, and called police at the first location where he could get service.  He then returned up to the trailhead to stand by.  I activated MCSO SAR Team 18, which is our ground team.  They responded with four members and met me in Idanha.  I briefed them and we headed to the trailhead.  Upon arrival, Team 18 departed up the trail.  Within about one hour, they had voice contact with MP.  They were able to locate her about 100 yards off the trail and bring her back down.  She was un-injured but slightly dehydrated.  She did not need medical attention.  She said she thought she was staying on the trail and then she got confused of location when the so called trail disappeared.  Nothing suspicious noted.

On September 15, 2012 at 1702 hours, I was dispatched to assist Beaverton Police Department with a missing eighty seven year old male.  It was reported that he had vascular dementia and non epileptic seizures.  His wife stated he had left for a walk four hours prior to calling and had not returned home.  Several officers arrived and conducted area checks of surrounding streets and neighborhoods.  I called for the assistance of NORSAR.  They brought two K9s.  Officers started attempting contact door to door while the Washington County SAR team was being called out.  At 2022 hours, we received a call from the male that he had walked over two miles from his residence and needed assistance.  An officer picked up [subject], he was well but slightly confused.  He was returned home with his wife.

On 09/20/12 at about 1700 hrs, a 63 year old Alzheimer's patient walked away from his wife while at Clackamas Town Center.  He was located 30 minutes later about a mile from the mall.  The subject was not from the area.  He was in good health.

Subject went missing around 0300 from residence.  Subject wandered to nearby apartment complex and knocked on the door.  She told the person who answered that she was cold and tired and wanted to be taken home to Dundee.  Subject lives in McMinnville.  Upon finding out that the subject did not know where in Dundee, she was taken back to McMinnville and taken to the McMinnville Police Station where Law enforcement and searchers were notified.

The Portland Police Bureau contact the Multnomah County Sheriff's Office requesting assistance on a missing 72 year old male with moderate dementia.  Portland Police requested the assistance of a trailing dog.  The 72 year old male was last seen around 1430 hours.  At about 1930 hours, SAR K9 unit from NORSAR started tracking for the missing 72 year old from the point last seen.  At about 2100 hours, a Portland Police Officer located the missing subject at the Cooper Penny in Portland.  The 72 year old male was reunited with family/friends.  The subject was not injured and due to his dementia, I was not able to get a statement from him regarding his whereabouts.

On November 2, 2012 I was dispatched to assist Cornelius Police with a missing subject.  It was reported that a seventy two year old male with Alzheimers was missing.  We arrived on scene and spoke with the reporting party.  We learned that the male had not been diagnosed with Alzheimers but did have some dementia.  The male had been missing a week prior as well and was located near the police department.  We were advised he did not have a cell phone, money or a wallet.  An attempt to locate was sent out to local agencies.  A Trimet officer advised dispatch that he had spoken with the male shortly before the attempt to locate was sent out.  He then re-contacted the male at the Four Seasons Bowling Center at 322 SE Washington St where he was recovered.  It appears the male took the Trimet bus to the location.

On 07/01/13 at around 1310 hours, Clackamas County Dispatch received a call about a missing female who was on a walk with her husband.  The reporting party stated that he was sitting on a log near the Salmon River when he noticed that his wife was no longer with him.  The reporting party informed me that he searched along the trail they were walking on and found no sight signs of her.  The RP also informed me that his wife suffers from dementia and that it is not normal for her to walk away on her own.  Clackamas County Search and Rescue was activated and responded to the scene at around 1515 hours.  Search teams were deployed in to the field at around 1540 hours along the trail were the subject was last seen.  At around 1612 hours searchers informed me that they had located the subject walking along a closed road near the trail she was walking on.  The subject was in good shape with no medical needs.

On 04/26/2013 at about 1115 hours it was reported that Lance McFarland left his residence at 13056 SE 119th Drive in Clackamas and had not returned.  Mr. McFarland was described as having Dementia and left his residence around 1000 hours.  His usual route was to walk around the neighborhood and then return.  CCSO Patrol and CCSO SAR were contacted and responded to the location and after searching about 15 minutes he was located about 12 blocks from home.

Man with multiple mental and behavioral disorders walked away from the Wood Village Manor Care Facility in Wood Village, OR.  A canvas by patrol revealed no clues.  He was entered as an Endangered Missing Person and flyers were distributed by the canvas, through the media and law enforcement channels.  The subject was located by police and returned to the facility.

Malheur County SAR received a call regarding an Alzheimer's patient who walked away from his home.  Ontario Police Department decided to wait because the male subject usually returns home.  A member of SAR activated us at 1410 to start looking for the male subject.  He was located behind some bushes at a residence near the Treasure Valley Community College unconscious with heat illness.

Polk Rapid Response Team found the 61 yr old male in the operational period.  Subject  had walked away from his care facility.  He has poor vision.  Lost his way back from a smoke break.  Found shelter in a old car.  He waited and was found a short time later.

On 04/27/13 at approximately 1900 Polk County SAR responded to the Spirit Mountain Casino to conduct a search for a 69 year old male with Dementia that had walked away from the casino.  On 04/27/13 at 1530 hours the male was last seen playing a slot machine on the gaming floor of the casino.  After casino staff search the business they reported the incident to the Grand Ronde Tribal Police Department which in turn contact the Polk County Sheriff's Office to request assistance by activating the SAR unit.  A call out was done and 18 members including a dog team responded to the location.  Just as the overhead team was starting to plan for the first assignments we received a tip that the missing person was seen walking down a road in the area.  Mobile assets at that point were task with conducting a hasty search of the roadway and located the male approximately five miles from the IPP.  He was in good health and returned to the CP where his wife was located.

On 01/23/13 at approximately 0330 hours I received a call from Washington County Sheriff's Office requesting assistance with a Search and Rescue Operation in their county.  Washington County was looking for a 69 year old male suffering from Dementia who had wandered from his home.  Clatsop County Search and Rescue Ground teams responded with a team of 3 for each of the remaining two days of the search.  The missing subject was located by Ground Search Teams on 01/24/13 at approximately 1215 hours.  Subject was reported deceased upon recovery.

On January 23 and 24 SAR members from Columbia County assisted Washington County search for a 69 year old male with dementia who had wandered off from the group home he lived at on January 22 in the afternoon.  He was found on the 24 deceased in a back yard swimming pool on January 24 by a SAR ground team.
Assistance to Washington County, to account for Yamhill County's Hours and Mileage.

On January 22, 2013 at about 1537 hrs, [subject] a 69yom with sever dementia left his carehome in Portland, Washington County, OR.  He left wandering in an unknown direction.  Multiple Patrol deputies, Beaverton PD K9 and 3 WCSO SAR members responded.  This was approximately an 45 hour Urban search which is located near Hwy 217 and SW Walker Rd just north of Beaverton.  Media was notified and flyers were distributed by WCSO crime prevention, church members, family and friends.  [subject] was last seen by neighbors within 1/2 mile on 1-22-13 at about 1545 hours.  On 1-24-13 at about 1215 hrs, ground search teams with Columbia County SAR located [subject] deceased in the back yard swimming pool at about 2038 feet from the IPP.  No signs of foul play or trauma were found to [subject].  During this entire search we utilized over head teams, ground search, road search, patrols, communications and several k9 teams.  7 paid & 2 volunteer WCSO SAR overhead team, 3 command staff, 1 PIO, 10 WCSO patrol, 5 WCSO Mobile Command Vehicle team members, 11 WCSO Explorers, 4 WCSO crime prevention, 10 Yamhill County SAR, 42 Multnomah County SAR, 3 Clackamas County SAR overhead, 6 Clatsop County SAR, 9 Marion County SAR, 11 Tillamook County SAR, 1 Polk County SAR, 2 Clark County SAR, 20 Pacific NW SAR, 6 Search One K9, 7 NORSAR K9, 2 Pacific Crest Search Dogs, 21 Mountain Wave Communications and 4x4 road search.  Base camp was set up and supported at Cedar Hill Baptist Church.  I had sent a request for additional Oregon and Washington State resources for the mission on 1-24-13 at 0600 which teams were responding but terminated once [subject] was located.

On 6/29/13 subject with Alzheimer's wandered away from the care facility she resides at on SW Canyon Road in Sheridan.  Caregiver had other residents in the house and could not look for her until the caregiver's spouse returned home.  Spouse searched then called the Sheriff's office.  Deputies responded to residence and searched immediate area.  Dispatch notified the on duty sergeant who was at the county shops where the Search and Rescue team had just returned from a training.  Search assignments were started and the team deployed immediately.  Subject was located by search team member walking the road tangled in blackberry bushes, medical support was requested and then team cut blackberry bushes so subject could be removed.

Female with dementia walked away from her residence.  Husband and neighbors searched and called our office for assistance.  Female was located by a citizen wandering aimlessly and transported to the hospital.
Assist Springfield PD in a search for a missing dementia walk away from a residence in Springfield.  As of this date, subject has not been located.

On 7/27/2013 at 1215 hours [reporting party] called to report his 77 year old wife who suffers from Alzheimer's had walked off and was now missing from their Silver Lake Highway home which is surrounded by Forest Service and Wildlife Refuge land.  Search and Rescue (SAR) teams were called out.  [subject] was located by SAR in good health not far from her residence on Silver Lake Highway.

78 y/o male with dementia walked away from his care facility.  Hasty search conducted of the surrounding area.  K-9 and ground team started their search from the PLS and discovered he had walked outside one door and back into the facility through another and was sleeping in another room.

Multnomah County Sheriff's Office SAR was requested by the Portland Police Bureau to assist in searching for a missing 80 year old female who suffers from dementia.  She was last seen at her house in NE Portland at 2230 hours on 08/06/13.  K9 team from Pacific Crest SAR assisted.  She was later spotted by a family friend walking on SE 82nd and SE Duke Street.  She was returned to her family.  She was interviewed by Portland Police, but they could not figure out how she travelled that distance.
[See report for details.]

On January 26, 2013 at about 0530 hrs, I was dispatched to assist Hillsboro PD with a Project lifesaver client [subject] an 80 year old female with dementia who left her care home.  [subject] was last seen at the residence at 2300 hrs on 1-25-13.  It was unknown when she left or what direction.  WCSO SAR volunteer Cutler responded with me to the residence.  A total of 16 WCSO and HPD patrol officers conducted containment and area checks.  1 WCSO K9 team and handler did a track, two Search one K9 teams and one NORSAR K9 team deployed on searching for [subject].  At about 0739 hrs, [subject] was found by Ofc. Zieman with HPD sitting on the front porch outside a home 2359 feet straight line from the care home.  [subject] was checked by medical and cleared.  She was transported back home by Patrol.

On 08-05-13, at about 2057 hours, Portland Police Bureau patrol was called on a reported missing 86 year old female who has late stages of Dementia.  The subject was last seen at about 2030 hours.  Family members searched the house and neighborhood for her and when they couldn't find her, they called the police.  SAR K9 was used from 2300 hours to 0100 hours with no success.  SAR ground members were activated in the early morning hours.  Portland Police Officers conducted a neighborhood canvass both on foot and in vehicles.  The subject was found by neighbors lying on the curb of a nearby street.  She was not injured, but taken to the hospital for evaluation.

\Subject reported as an Alzheimer's walkaway from the Central Point Holiday Inn.  SAR hasty units did not deploy as the subject was located after a follow up investigation by the IC in a room next door at the hotel.  He was found peacefully sleeping.  1.5 Hours

On 05/08/13 at about 1500 hrs, an 86 year old woman with Alzheimer's was reported missing from her residence in Milwaukie.  A search was started in the urban area near her home.  At about 2000 hrs, we were able to contact the missing subject's estranged brother in Sandy and learned the missing woman was with him.

[Subject] was reported missing from his residence in Fall Crk.  [Subject] suffers from dementia and has walked away before.  [Subject] was located in Springfield, Oregon.  It is believed that [Subject] obtained a ride from an unknown person or was picked up from an unknown person and dropped off in the Springfield area.  When [Subject] was located he was not sure of his whereabouts or how he got there.  His son was called and picked his father up.  The son stated his father suffers from dementia and thanked us for our quick response in looking for his father.  IPP/10T0518743E/4866210N WGS 84 elev.750.  (This is victims residence.  Find-IPP/ 10T0497760E/4879731N WGS 84, elev. 442.

On March 13th, 2013 I was dispatched to assist Hillsboro Police Department with a missing dementia subject.  [Subject] wife called at 1145 hours, reporting that her husband left at 1015 hours and had not returned. [Subject] is a project lifesaver client and wears a tracking bracelet.  We checked the immediate area and did not receive a signal.  Deputies and Officers checked local parks, roads, and shopping areas with out any luck.  We believed [Subject] was able to travel outside of the area of where we were attempted with our project lifesaver equipment.  We started to spread our search out. At 1455 hours, dispatch received a call of a suspicious person walking on Glencoe Rd near Scotch Church road.  A deputy contacted the male and identified him as our missing subject.  [Subject] was returned home. I contacted [Subject].  He stated he believed he had been gone two hours and had walked an extra wide loop and believed he was headed home.

On 09/04/13 at about 1645 hrs a 97 year old woman walked away from a store while shopping with her daughter.  She got onto a bus and was dropped off in Portland.  I searched the area and found her wandering in a residential neighborhood.  She told me she was on her way home in Kirkland Delaware.

The missing subject walked away from her house at approx 11:00 on 8-24-13.  Husband initially thought that she was gardening.  She was reported as missing at 19:59.  A JCSAR search was started at approx. 02:00 on 8-25-13.  Subject self rescued at approx 09:15 by calling 911.  Mounted SAR was called in at 0500 hours on 8/25.  Josephine County SAR was also called into assist, but was stood down right after.  7.25 Hours.

Subject Sub-Category: Suspect suicide,  why someone would have climbed into well.
driver of a car reported overdue from a trip
8 year old female suffering from Altziemers, hearing loss

Lost Strategy: Maintained one specific route,No planned strategy

Subject Sub-Category: Male was in a disoriented state when he knocked on door on the night before he went missing.

Comments: At about 1100 hours on Sunday 11 July 2010, a brother and step brother went off  for a walk to nearby Bothamley Park near the Kenepuru Stream. They took two  dogs with them and were expected back in the afternoon. When they had not returned by late afternoon, family went out looking for them.  When they failed to locate them, they contacted Police. SAR were notified and just after the Police arrived at the address, the two  boys turned up at their home address. They had taken a wrong turn and were heading towards the Hutt, then one of the  dogs slowed their progress and it became dark which further slowed their  progress. They had not taken a cell phone, so were not able to contact anyone  to collect them.

subject walked from Anawhata Rd  along coastline south then decided to climb up  cliff to return to vehicle . halfway up got stuck and was running out of light  . Started panicing and called police . helicopter sent and winched him off then  returned him to his car

Subject was participating in an event run by the Taupo Hunt Club.  She fell off  her horse, then the horse rolled on her.  She fractured her arm in two places.   A helicopter was used to rescue her because of l imited road access. She was  flown to Waikato Hospital.

2 workers constructing new tracks and steps at top of the mount using a "high lift dumper" the dumper was on the edge which colapsed and the driver jumped off as it went over the edge, the driver and co-worker (the victim) were trying to get to a position where they could see the machine. Victim stumpled on some vegatation and fell about 40-50 meters. He landed on top of the machine.  Had to be carried back up in a basket and ropes. Air lifted to Tauranga Hospital
Subject's car located at beach.  Inquiries showed despondant behaviour. Area of bush surrounding car to be searched while further inquiries conducted. Subject located at uncle's address in Papamoa

In addition to attached report, clothing the subject was wearing when he ran was subsequently located by the investigating team back up in the dwellings where he had been staying so he must have been able to climb out over night and decamp again. Handed himslef into Tauranga Police on the friday evening

Brougham is a 27yo woman who is Bipolar and was suffering from a hyper manic episode. She stripped off her clothes and headed off to the nearby Manawatu River which was in flood at the time. Police, R.E.S.T., Palmerston North Rescue Helicopter and SAR members responded. Subject was located 3 hrs later when she walked to an address in Jackytown Road. It appears that she'd been in the river for about 800m but luckily eddied out on a bend. She then got out and walked across farmland to the house. She was standing on the front porch, cold and distressed, when seen by a local who was out walking a dog.

informant called police after he thought he saw a parachute on the port hills below castle rock.  stated he didn't see parachute in the air or fall to the ground, just looked like a parachute, he pointed out the area to police and through binoculars a digger could be seen to be working in the area described.  in a different area above the road and behind castle rock the informant spotted an acutal parachute lying on the ground.  units were directed to this area.  through the binoculars is was clear to see the parachutist walking aroung with his chute. ,O'SHAUGHNSSY was spoken and stated he was waiting for the wind to come right and he hadn't attempted to take off yet.,Unit's were sent imediatley to the informant to asses the situation however while units were on route the westpac chopper was dispatched.,There was apparently another informant via either fire service or ambo, but more details on this informant weren't avaliable.,After reading the job text, it is my opinion that the police informant was looking at a digger arm and mistook it for a parachute as he described the colour and location for it correctly.  O'SHAUGHNSSY was spotted a short time later in a different location and had a different colour chute, i think he just happened to be up there and was seen.

The missing party is intellectually handicapped having the mental age of a teenager. He has been taken on a walk by his adopted twin sister and her partner. He has walked off quickly and separated. He has then stopped and waited for them to catch up. When they did he was told to stay with them. He laughed and took off again. Their destination was Apple tree Bay and they assumed that he would meet them there. When they got there he wasnt there. They waited and then returned to the car thinking that he would meet up with them on the track. They then called Police and advised them.Whilst teams were being assembled the partner walked back in and located the missing party on the tinline lookout ,tired and confused. They have then walked out, meeting up with the search team as they did so. The missing party was tired and suffered no physical injuries.

At about 1000hrs TAUROA was seen at the Aspen retirement home having morning tea. He was noticed missng at 1200noon. Staff and family conducted a search and TAUROA was not located. Police SAR was notified at 1730hours. TAUROA was located by staff 24 kms from the LKP up Pyes Pa Road. ,This is the second time TAUROA has gone missing in 6 months. A call was received from North Comms to Rotorua SAR regarding a possibly overdue hunting party in the Ruatahuna area.,There was mention made there may have been a person overdue from a rafting/hunting trip.,After numerous enquiries it was determined that Comms hade confused two separate jobs, one was a drowning in the Motu River the previous day, the second a hunter who had called in to say he had been overdue, but was now safely out of the bush after being delayed at Te Totara Hut due to flooded rivers.

2x motorcyclists from Timaru intended to ride from Kyeburn, Buster gorge, over the Hawkdun Range and to exit at Hills Creek. Riders intended to take about 4 hours to complete ride, and did not have warm clothing or food. Intended time of completion of ride was to be 1200 lunchtime. Instructions were left with associate who was to collect them from Hills Creek, that if they were not out by 1400hours, then the associate should begin to make enquiries. Motorcyclists encountered difficult terrain throughout the ride, including significant snowdrifts that they were unable to negotiate. This caused them to be forced to return to where they started at/near Kyeburn. Motorcyclists were located at around 1830hrs.

Party of 3 travelling up Mahaukura track, from lodge.  Travelling to Pahautea hut overnight.  Enroute TANGLAO became unwell stomach cramps, fever, vommitting/diarrhoea.  Contact made by cellphone.  Taupo rescue helicopter initially dispatched to assist rescue, however conditions not condusive and stood down.  Party located adjacent to track and aided.  Walked out following morning

South Coms advise of an overdue fisherman who had intended to go to Cave Stream, near Castle Hill, then walk down Broken River and fish, he was due to arrive at Cave Stream at 0500hrs and then be back for dinner that night. AXR checked the car park at Cave Stream, locating his car, a friend of the missing person who usually companies him is contacted, he has detailed information of his intentions and can assist Police in search planning. Information from this person advises that the missing person although a keen fisherman is limited bush craft and outdoors experience, there are also many hazards in the area, bluffs, cliffs and gorgy river systems. It is also believed he has limited clothing with him.,A SAR advisor is contacted and a search is planned for a search of the area in the morning. 4 search teams including 2 search dog teams are put into the area. A helicopter from garden City is also tasked to assist with deploying teams and searching the gorgy river sections and bluff drop off zones. Approximately 25 people involved in the search,The helicopter used is an R44, the smallest resource available for a search of this nature in this area.,Later that morning the missing party arrives at the search base being dropped off by a member of the public, he advised that he became completely disorientated and lost, he walked for many hours in the wrong direction, slept rough overnight, and he had superficial injuries including scratches minor cuts, abrasions and dehydration. This was due to him having fallen several times down scree and steep terrain. He had also been swept down a river for about 100 metres before being able to recover and get out of the water. He was lucky not to have suffered more extensive injuries or perished.

The subject suffers from Aspergers syndrome. [symptons include inability to communicate properly, & abnormal/unusual behaviour]  She was on a school trip and visiting the Kerosene Creek thermal area for a swim.,She suffered some sort of upset which caused her to wander off from the group.,After a cursory search by staff Police were called & SAR put on standby pending a trial dog track.,The subject was tracked and located by a Police dog close to where she had gone missing.
Subject fell while descending Ngauruhoe.  He cut his face and head.  Located by rescue helicopter and flown to Taumarunui Hospital.

Subject was reported missing after she disappeared from her home.  At the time her mother was in hospital and her step father in custody - she was being cared for by a neighbour from 29 Rawhiti Street.  On the afternoon of 13.11.10 the caregiver took the girl home and she disppeared sometime between 5 and 6 pm.  She was last seen playing on the trampoline and eating a sandwich. She was reported missing 2.5 hours later.  ,An IMT was established at the Taupo Police Station and teams of LandSAR Volunteers and Police searched the streets, parks, schools, kindergartens, reserves and river banks until 2am on 14.11.10.  Police continued searching neighbouring houses until 3am and then suspended the search for the night with the intention of recommencing mid morning.  Several members of the public joined the search during the night when they found out that the girl was missing.,Just after 7am Police were advised that family found the girl playing in the grounds of the Laughton Street kindergarten.

On the 26th November 2010 at about 9.30pm Vaughan took three others 4wd around the south coast of Wellington.,At approximately 10.20pm Vaughan lost control of his vehicle and crashed causing significant damage. All the occupants were uninjured but what followed the crash was a bizzare call for help from Vaughan via Texting to a friend stating they had had a crash and one person was bleeding from the head.,The person receiving the text called Police but lead them on merry chase trying to establish what and who needed help.,After alot of perseverence from Comms they finally got enough information out of the caller to establish there had been a crash and there was possibly someone injured.,The Maritime Unit was notified and headed around in the 4wd to the south coast. The fire service and Ambulance were all in attendance and had called out their 4wd vehicles.,The crashed 4wd was located just west of Devils gate by Police and the occupants were found not far from the crash sitting with another group  who had a bon fire going.,It was established quickly that no one was injured. The car was written off and that the four did not want any assistance.,They refused to be checked by ambulance and refused a ride back to the car park. ,All Ambulance and fire staff were stood down and returned back to the carpark.,Comment:,These people were basically time wasters, although they had had a crash the sending of the text started a near full scale response from emergency services that wasn't necessary. In which this group did not care the slightest.

WOOD was a member of St Kentigerns College school camp at Mt Ruapehu for the week. The college employed the services of a Ruapehu Alpine Rescue Organisation member to guide the group of students to the Crater Lake for a day walk.,WOOD has just collapsed for no known reason. Initial First Aid rendered to WOOD on site while waiting for a snow groomer to come and transport her from the mountain.,Once off the mountain no further medical treatment needed.,Similar incident occurred two days later and WOOD was flown to hospital by the Taupo rescue chopper from the Waihohonu Springs area.,WOOD surrently undergoing tests including CAT scans in Auckland to help diagnosis what is wrong with her.

Subject was a 64 year old cabinet maker who was slightly depressed and had the beginnings of Alzheimers. He had seemed normal to his wife but had been struggling with life in general; asking for more help to do odd jobs and told her he was not coping with the work on their farm. He left for work on Monday morning and failed to return in the evening.,His car was found on the outskirts of Woodville, abandoned, with the keys in the ignition. He was an avid tramper and had tramped all over with his boys. Very familiar with the Tararua Ranges.  No idea why he would leave his car at Woodville, although he had tramped the Coppermine Creek before.,Subject was not on any medication except for Omega 3 and Chondroitin for his joints.,They had a daughter who had a heart condition and died at the pools. Her boyfriend shot himself about a month later. It was nearing the anniversary of those deaths.,Subject walked up and down the creek looking for a place to drown hinself. He tried one small pool but could not override the reflex to save hiimself. His false teeth were found in that pool. ,He walked back downstream about 100m to another pool and this time picked up and held in his arms a large rock. He was able to trap his arms under the rock with his body weight which was sufficient to enable his drowning.

Lost party following track. Female losses balance and falls down bank dragging

Lost party followed river for a short period. Realised that they were lost and 

remained in that position until located.



Search method: Tracks all check prior to the arrival of SAR squad by Police and 

locals. Not located. Due to age and medical concerns of lost party urgent 

response required. Helicopter dispatched to scene. Lost party located in river 

bed. Nil injuries



Debrief: Held after search. Nothing of interest. Area easily contained. Only 

concern is that any tracks were destroyed by locals searching in the first 

instant. This cannot be avoided and must expect that this will happen given 

circumstances.
